Pekannya film drama politk dengan balutan sejarah. Sebelum Hari Jumat ada Darkest Hour yang mulai tayang, perhari ini Ada '1987 When The Day Come' yang tayang dijaringan CGV dan Cinemaxx.

Berdasarkan peristiwa nyata seputar gerakan mahasiswa dan gerakan pro-demokrasi Juni 1987 yang menjadi penyebab berakhirnya rezim militer Presiden Chun Doo-hwan. Protes mahasiswa dimulai ketika terungkap bahwa aktivis mahasiswa Park Jong-chul, yang berpartisipasi dalam demonstrasi pro-demokrasi melawan rezim tersebut, disiksa hingga meninggal dalam sesi interogasi. Polisi dan pemerintah pada awalnya berusaha untuk menyembunyikan kasus Park Jong-Chul, namun media dan mahasiswa berusaha untuk mengungkapkan kebenaran¬¶ https://t.co/M5D6unPF10 https://t.co/bezqvu5xYS
Translated Text:
This week is a political drama film with a historical setting. Before Friday there was Darkest Hour which started broadcasting, today there is '1987 When The Day Come' which is broadcast on the CGV and Cinemaxx networks.

Based on real events surrounding the student movement and pro-democracy movement in June 1987 which was the cause of the end of President Chun Doo-hwan's military regime. Student protests began when it was revealed that student activist Park Jong-chul, who participated in pro-democracy demonstrations against the regime, was tortured to death during an interrogation session. The police and government initially tried to hide the Park Jong-Chul case, but the media and students tried to reveal the truth¬¶ https://t.co/M5D6unPF10 https://t.co/bezqvu5xYS
